# API Design Conventions

## URL Structure

All endpoints under `/api/` prefix. App-specific routing:

```
/api/auth/          accounts (login, register, profile, classes)
/api/assessment/    assessments, questions, submissions
/api/adaptive/      BKT states, pathways, next-task
/api/curriculum/    courses, concepts, milestones, micro-tasks
/api/dashboard/     early warnings, interventions, lecturer views
/api/analytics/     KPIs, reports, data quality
/api/events/        event logs, learning analytics
/api/wellbeing/     study nudges, wellbeing status
/api/privacy/       consent, export, deletion requests
/api/health/        system health check
```

## Request/Response

- Pagination: `PageNumberPagination` with `page_size=20`, params `?page=N`
- Filtering: `DjangoFilterBackend` + `SearchFilter` + `OrderingFilter`
- Error format: consistent shape from `privacy_exception_handler`
- Dates: ISO 8601 format, timezone-aware (Asia/Ho_Chi_Minh)

## Authentication & Authorization

- JWT via httpOnly cookies (`CookieJWTAuthentication`)
- Default: `IsAuthenticated` globally
- RBAC per-view: student sees own data only, lecturer sees assigned classes only
- Admin-only: schema/docs endpoints in production

```python
from accounts.permissions import IsStudent, IsLecturer, IsAdminUser

class StudentProgressView(APIView):
    permission_classes = [IsAuthenticated, IsStudent]
```

## API Contract Rules

- Every endpoint must have: happy path, 401, 403 (if RBAC), 404, 400 test cases
- List endpoints must test pagination
- No breaking changes: never remove routes, change response types, add required fields, or change HTTP methods without versioning
- OpenAPI schema at `/api/schema/` (drf-spectacular)
- Use `@extend_schema()` to document custom actions

## Throttling

Already configured per-class rates:
- `anon`: 30/min
- `user`: 120/min
- `login`: 10/min, `register`: 5/min
- `assessment_submit`: 30/min, `export`: 5/min

Apply custom throttle classes for sensitive endpoints:

```python
from rest_framework.throttling import ScopedRateThrottle

class LoginView(APIView):
    throttle_scope = "login"
```

## Serializer Best Practices

- Explicit `fields` tuple, never `"__all__"`
- Read-only fields for computed/auto values
- Nested serializers for related objects (depth=1 max)
- Write-specific serializers when input differs from output
- Validate BKT bounds in adaptive serializers (0 <= p <= 1, guess+slip < 1)
